Author: jl777c#5810
Content: @ComputerGenie ok, I think I really fixed the spontaneaous bob issue. internally now there are separate sets of prices for alice vs bob, so if you are not doing bob things like autoprice there wont be any bob price to ordermatch

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: before there was a single set of prices so if you did an alice order, it ended up with a bob price for the reverse for a short period of time and if an incoming alice request came in, it could have started the ordermatch process. But I think it would not have completed as there wasnt a pending alice order i that direction.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: now it wont even start

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: jl777 branch

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: added persistence to gtc orders, but it is untested. if it works or doesnt, let me know. basically it will restore any pending GTC order, but it is quite inefficient for now if you have a lot of orders
